Yes, you can use a smooth windowing function to gradually transition between the two frequencies. Here's an updated MATLAB code that uses a Hann window function to create a smoother transition:
```
% Set parameters
fs = 44100; % Sample rate
dur = 30; % Duration in seconds
f1 = 300; % Starting frequency
f2 = 200; % Lowest frequency
f3 = 300; % Ending frequency
% Create time vector
t = 0:1/fs:dur-1/fs;
% Create frequency vector
f = linspace(f1,f2,length(t)/2);
f = [f linspace(f2,f3,length(t)/2)];
% Create melody with smooth transition
win = hann(length(f)).';
freq = f.*win;
y = sin(2*pi*freq.*t);
% Save audio file
audiowrite('soothing_melody.wav',y,fs);
```
This code uses the Hann window function to gradually transition from the starting frequency to the lowest frequency and then back up to the ending frequency, resulting in a smoother melody.

